T1  - Disagreement in the Equity Options Market and Stock Returns
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab078
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 35
IS  - 3
SP  - 1443
EP  - 1479
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We estimate investor disagreement from synthetic long and short stock trades in the equity options market. We show that high disagreement predicts low stock returns after positive earnings surprises and high stock returns after negative earnings surprises. The negative effect is stronger for high-beta stocks and stocks that are more difficult to sell short. In the cross-section of all stocks and the subset of the 500 largest companies, high disagreement robustly predicts low monthly and weekly stock returns.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab078
ER  - 



