TY  - JOUR
AU  - Atmaz, Adem
T1  - Stock Return Extrapolation, Option Prices, and Variance Risk Premium
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab051
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 35
IS  - 3
SP  - 1348
EP  - 1393
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This paper presents a tractable dynamic equilibrium model of stock return extrapolation in the presence of stochastic volatility. In the model, consistent with survey evidence, investors expect future returns to be higher (lower) but also less (more) volatile following positive (negative) stock returns. The biased volatility expectation introduces a new channel through which past returns and investor sentiment affect derivative prices. In particular, through this novel channel, the model reconciles the otherwise puzzling evidence of past returns affecting option prices and the evidence of variance risk premium predicting future stock market returns even after controlling for the realized variance.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab051
ER  - 



